          "settings": {
            "heading": "A Heritage Centuries in the Making",
            "highlight_font": "body",
            "seo_heading": "h2",
            "size": "h2",
            "content": "<p>Hand block printing is an ancient textile art form that dates back thousands of years, with roots deeply embedded in Indian craftsmanship. This meticulous technique has been passed down through generations of artisan families, each keeper of this tradition adding their own vision while honoring the sacred methods of their ancestors.</p><p>What began as a means to decorate fabrics for royalty has evolved into a celebrated art form that bridges the past and present. Each piece tells a story - of patient hands carving intricate designs into wooden blocks, of natural dyes extracted from earth and plant, and of the rhythmic press of block against cloth that creates patterns both timeless and unique.</p><p>In an era of mass production, hand block printing stands as a testament to the irreplaceable value of human touch. Every print carries the subtle variations that make it authentic, the slight imperfections that prove its handmade origins, and the soul of the artisan who crafted it.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
