        "text_nbxhTC": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p><strong>1. Carving the Block: </strong>Master artisans hand-carve intricate designs into seasoned wood, a process requiring years of skill and unwavering precision.</p><p><strong>2. Preparing the Dye: </strong>Natural dyes are carefully extracted from plants, minerals, and earth, mixed to achieve rich, lasting colors that honor tradition.</p><p><strong>3. The Printing Ritual: </strong>With practiced rhythm, the artisan dips the block in dye and presses it firmly onto fabric, repeating this dance to create patterns.</p><p><strong>4. Setting & Finishing: </strong>The printed fabric is treated and washed, allowing colors to set and bloom into their final, vibrant expression.</p>"
